[{"location":"proteins/","page":"Proteins","title":"Proteins","text":"EditURL = \"https://github.com/kool7d/BioMakie.jl/blob/master/src/proteins.jl\"","category":"page"},{"location":"proteins/","page":"Proteins","title":"Proteins","text":"using JSServe\nPage(exportable=true, offline=true)","category":"page"},{"location":"proteins/","page":"Proteins","title":"Proteins","text":"After the page got displayed by the frontend, we can start with creating plots and JSServe Apps:","category":"page"},{"location":"proteins/","page":"Proteins","title":"Proteins","text":"using WGLMakie\n# Set the default resolution to something that fits the Documenter theme\nset_theme!(resolution=(800, 400))\nscatter(1:4, color=1:4)","category":"page"},{"location":"proteins/","page":"Proteins","title":"Proteins","text":"As you can see, the output is completely static, because we don't have a running Julia server, as it would be the case with e.g. Pluto. To make the plot interactive, we will need to write more parts of WGLMakie in JS, which is an ongoing effort. As you can see, the interactivity already keeps working for 3D:","category":"page"},{"location":"proteins/","page":"Proteins","title":"Proteins","text":"N = 60\nfunction xy_data(x, y)\n    r = sqrt(x^2 + y^2)\n    r == 0.0 ? 1f0 : (sin(r)/r)\nend\nl = range(-10, stop = 10, length = N)\nz = Float32[xy_data(x, y) for x in l, y in l]\nsurface(\n    -1..1, -1..1, z,\n    colormap = :Spectral\n)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = BioMakie","category":"page"},{"location":"#BioMakie","page":"Home","title":"BioMakie","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Installation-and-Setup","page":"Home","title":"Installation and Setup","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This package contains interactive biological visualizations and using Makie. This package is in development and not yet \"production ready\". If you want to test it out use add BioMakie#master instead of add BioMakie for the moment.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"julia> ] add BioMakie#master\r\njulia> using BioMakie","category":"page"},{"location":"#Usage","page":"Home","title":"Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"To view a PDB structure, use the viewstruc function with a PDB ID.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"julia> sv = viewstruc(\"2VB1\")","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"(Image: Image of struc)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"To view a multiple sequence alignment, use the viewmsa function with a Pfam ID.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"julia> mv = viewmsa(\"PF00062\")","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"(Image: Image of msa)","category":"page"}]
